2 SENATE BILL 905
1 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
2 BY adding to
3 Article – State Finance and Procurement
4 Section 6–226(a)(2)(iii)214.
5 Annotated Code of Maryland
6 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
7 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
8 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
9 Article – Economic Development
10 10–417.
11 (A) (1) THERE IS A MARYLAND ADVANCED MANUFACTURING GRANT
12 PROGRAM.
13 (2) THE SUBJECT TO SUBSECTION (F) OF THIS SECTION, THE
14 CORPORATION SHALL ADMINISTER THE PROGRAM.
15 (B) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO SUPPORT THE GROWTH OF
16 COMPANIES THAT SPECIALIZE IN REGENERATIVE MEDICINE AND OTHER ADVANCED
17 MANUFACTURING.
18 (C) THE CORPORATION, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE MARYLAND STEM
19 CELL RESEARCH COMMISSION, SHALL ESTABLISH:
20 (1) ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA TO RECEIVE A GRANT UNDER THE
21 PROGRAM;
22 (2) GRANT APPLICATION PROCEDURES AND EVALUATION CRITERIA;
23 AND
24 (3) GRANT AWARD PROCESSES AND AMOUNTS.
25 (D) GRANT RECIPIENTS MAY USE GRANT PROCEEDS ONLY FOR:
26 (1) THE ACQUISITION, RENOVATION, OR CONSTRUCTION OF SPACE
27 FOR REGENERATIVE MEDICINE OR OTHER ADVANCED MANUFACTURING;
28 (2) INFRASTRUCTURE IMPROVEMENTS NECESSARY TO SUPPORT
29 REGENERATIVE MEDICINE OR OTHER ADVANCED MANUFACTURING; AND

SENATE BILL 905 3
1 (3) THE EQUIPMENT NECESSARY FOR REGENERATIVE MEDICINE OR
2 OTHER ADVANCED MANUFACTURING.
3 (E) (1) IN THIS SUBSECTION, “FUND” MEANS THE MARYLAND ADVANCED
4 MANUFACTURING GRANT PROGRAM FUND.
5 (2) THERE IS A MARYLAND ADVANCED MANUFACTURING GRANT
6 PROGRAM FUND.
7 (3) THE PURPOSE OF THE FUND IS TO PROVIDE GRANTS UNDER THIS
8 SECTION.
9 (4) THE CORPORATION SHALL ADMINISTER THE FUND.
10 (5) (I) THE FUND IS A SPECIAL, NONLAPSING FUND THAT IS NOT
11 SUBJECT TO § 7–302 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
12 (II) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL HOLD THE FUND
13 SEPARATELY, AND THE COMPTROLLER SHALL ACCOUNT FOR THE FUND.
14 (6) THE FUND CONSISTS OF:
15 (I) MONEY APPROPRIATED IN THE STATE BUDGET TO THE
16 FUND;
17 (II) INTEREST EARNINGS; AND
18 (III) ANY OTHER MONEY FROM ANY OTHER SOURCE ACCEPTED
19 FOR THE BENEFIT OF THE FUND.
20 (7) THE FUND MAY BE USED ONLY FOR:
21 (I) GRANTS UNDER THIS SECTION; AND
22 (II) THE COSTS INCURRED BY THE CORPORATION TO
23 ADMINISTER THE PROGRAM.
24 (8) (I) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL INVEST THE MONEY OF THE
25 FUND IN THE SAME MANNER AS OTHER STATE MONEY MAY BE INVESTED.
26 (II) ANY INTEREST EARNINGS OF THE FUND SHALL BE
27 CREDITED TO THE FUND.

4 SENATE BILL 905
1 (9) EXPENDITURES FROM THE FUND MAY BE MADE ONLY IN
2 ACCORDANCE WITH THE STATE BUDGET.
3 (F) THE CORPORATION SHALL CONSULT WITH THE MARYLAND STEM CELL
4 RESEARCH COMMISSION ONLY ON ITEMS RELATED TO REGENERATIVE MEDICINE
5 UNDER THE PROGRAM, INCLUDING:
6 (1) ESTABLISHING CRITERIA OR PROCEDURES SPECIFIC TO
7 REGENERATIVE MEDICINE UNDER THIS SECTION; AND
8 (2) ADOPTING REGULATIONS REGARDING REGENERATIVE MEDICINE
9 UNDER THIS SECTION.
10 (G) THE CORPORATION, IN CONSULTATION WITH THE MARYLAND STEM
11 CELL COMMISSION, MAY ADOPT REGULATIONS NECESSARY TO CARRY OUT THIS
12 SECTION.
13 Article – State Finance and Procurement
14 6–226.
15 (a) (2) (i) This paragraph does not apply in fiscal years 2024 through 2028.
16 (ii) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, and unless
17 inconsistent with a federal law, grant agreement, or other federal requirement or with the
18 terms of a gift or settlement agreement, net interest on all State money allocated by the
19 State Treasurer under this section to special funds or accounts, and otherwise entitled to
20 receive interest earnings, as accounted for by the Comptroller, shall accrue to the General
21 Fund of the State.
22 (iii) The provisions of subparagraph (ii) of this paragraph do not
23 apply to the following funds:
24 212. the Department of Social and Economic Mobility Special
25 Fund; [and]
26 213. the Population Health Improvement Fund; AND
27 214. THE MARYLAND ADVANCED MANUFACTURING
28 GRANT PROGRAM FUND.
29 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
30 1, 2026.

